  %h3 Gin Flight:
  %p ‘Why Cucumbers Are Better Than Men’
  %p A hilariously named book by Risa Glickman. The cucumber repre- sented by the Gin in the middle of this relationship - Hendricks. This modern Gin flight is showing off some more ‘modern’ styles of Gin where the master distiller will sometimes use unique botanicals (fruit/ herb/spice) to change the structure/flavour of the Gin. We start with London’s tea influenced Beefeater 24, then follow with Hendricks from Scotland, which uses rose and cucumber in its botanical mix, and finish with Geranium also from London that uses the geranium flower to add a unique and alternative flavour.
  %p.tasting-price Beefeater 24 | Hendricks Gin | Geranium Gin


